DUBAI: US actress Lindsay Lohan opened up this week about her wedding plans as she prepares to tie the knot with Dubai-based financier Bader Shammas. For the latest updates, follow us on Instagram @arabnews.lifestyle The “Mean Girls” actress announced her engagement to Shammas in November on Instagram. A post shared by Lindsay Lohan (@lindsaylohan) In an interview with Extra, Lohan said she has started her hunt for venues and gowns. “I’m looking at destinations. I’ve already started talking to a friend of mine about the dress,” she said. “But I want to do things right and I want to pace everything.” A post shared by Lindsay Lohan (@lindsaylohan) The Hollywood star also said that she plans to sport several dresses on her big day. The couple were first spotted together at a music festival in Dubai shortly before the pandemic hit in 2020.